17,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"وَدّ","root":"ودد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41787","n41788","n41789"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to love, to like","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wish, to like to have, to love would it be there, to be comfortable with, to desire (+لَوْ (law))","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"يَوَدُّ أَحَدُهُمْ لَوْ يُعَمَّرُ أَلْفَ سَنَةً","english":"One of them would like it were he made to live thousand years"},{"text":"رُبَمَا يَوَدُّ الَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا لَوْ كَانُوا مُسْلِمِينَ","english":"Perhaps those who disbelieve will wish they had been Muslims."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of وَدَّ (wadda) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"love, affection, friendship","examples":[{"text":"إِذَا مَا ٱلنَّاسُ جَرَّبَهُمْ لَبِيبُ / فَإِنِّي قَدْ أَكَلْتُهُمُ وَذَاقَا / فَلَمْ أَرَ وُدَّهُمْ إِلَّا خِدَاعًا / وَلَمْ أَرَ دِينَهُمْ إِلَّا نِفَاقَا"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"desire, wish"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dialectal form of وَتَد (watad)","tags":["dialectal","form-of"],"examples":[{"text":"خالي لقيطٌ (var. عُوَيْف) وأبو عَلِجِّ … المطعمان اللحمَ بالعَشِجِّ\nوبالغداةِ كِسَرَ (var. فِلَق) البَرْنِجِّ … يُقْلَعُ بالوَدِّ وبالصِّيصجِّ","english":"I have two uncles ʿUwayf and Abū ʿAlī … who eat meat in the vesper,\nAnd in the morn sweet shives of dates … they pluck by means of pegs and pales"}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Wadd, one of the five false gods worshipped by the people of Noah.","examples":[{"text":"وَقَالُوا لَا تَذَرُنَّ ءَالِهَتَكُمْ وَلَا تَذَرُنَّ وَدًّا وَلَا سُوَاعًا وَلَا يَغُوثَ وَيَعُوقَ وَنَسْرًا","english":"and said (to their people), “Never forsake your gods, and never forsake Wadd, nor Suwā‘, nor Yaghūth and Ya‘ūq and Nasr.”"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/wadd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41787","headword_ar":"وِدٌّ","root":"wd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wud~N","text_ar":"وُدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wad~N","text_ar":"وَدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IJ, L, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadiydN","text_ar":"وَدِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) A person"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beloved; an object of love; a friend;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~N","text_ar":"خِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiybN","text_ar":"حَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadiyqN","text_ar":"صَدِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHab~N","text_ar":"مُحَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K: in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHib~N","text_ar":"مُحِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  Also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wudN","text_ar":"وُدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waduwdN","text_ar":"وَدُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadiydN","text_ar":"وَدِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAd~N","text_ar":"وَادٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kz) A person"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who loves; loving; affectionate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, TA:) the first also used in a pl. sense, (L, K,) being [originally] an inf. n. (TA) and the second used alike as masc. and fem. (S, L, Msb.) ―         -b3-  Also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wud~N","text_ar":"وُدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuduwdN","text_ar":"وُدُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miwad~N","text_ar":"مِوَدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) also written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawad~N","text_ar":"مَوَدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF,) A man (TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loving much; having much love"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection; very loving"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affectionate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, MF.) ―         -b4-  Pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awodaAdN","text_ar":"اَوْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wid~N","text_ar":"وِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and also a pl. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wud~N","text_ar":"وُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in the second of the above senses; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadaAdN","text_ar":"وَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wad~N","text_ar":"وَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadiydN","text_ar":"وَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in the first of the above senses; (L;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awud~N","text_ar":"اَوُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wud~N","text_ar":"وُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) in the second of the above senses; (K;) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wid~N","text_ar":"وِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awod~N","text_ar":"اَوْدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) [an irreg. pl., or quasi-pl. n., upon which I find no remark,] in the first of the above senses, (L,) or the second; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wud~aAdN","text_ar":"وُدَّادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAd~N","text_ar":"وَادٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Kz;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awid~aA='u","text_ar":"اَوِدَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadiydN","text_ar":"وَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) in the first of the above senses, (L,) or in the second; (L;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awid~apN","text_ar":"اَوِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) also pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadiydN","text_ar":"وَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) in the second of the above senses; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wudadaA='u","text_ar":"وُدَدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waduwdN","text_ar":"وَدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) in the second of the above senses, (S, K,) [and the third]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadiydN","text_ar":"وَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also mentioned as a pl. in the second of the above senses in the K; but this is probably a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"widaAdN","text_ar":"وِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-  IAth says, that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wud~N","text_ar":"وُدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", used as an epithet, is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw wud~K","text_ar":"ذُو وُدٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wid~N","text_ar":"وِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"does not require"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*w","text_ar":"ذو"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be understood, being syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadiyqN","text_ar":"صَدِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","IJ","TA","Msb","Kz","MF"]},{"entry_id":"n41788","headword_ar":"وَدٌّ","root":"wd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wid~N","text_ar":"وِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wad~N","text_ar":"وَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wud~N","text_ar":"وُدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the former is the more common, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain idol"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which pertained to the people of Noah, and then to Kelb, and was at Doomet-el-Jendel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain good man, who lived between Adam and Noah, and of whom, after his death, was made an image, which, after a long time, became an object of worship;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwaAEN","text_ar":"سُوَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaguwvu","text_ar":"يَغُوثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEuwqu","text_ar":"يَعُوقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasorN","text_ar":"نَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned therewith in the Kur, lxxi. 22 and 23: (Bd:) and the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain idol belonging to Kureysh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ud~N","text_ar":"اُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biwad~iki","text_ar":"بِوَدِّكِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By thy Wedd!"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the idol so named. (L.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wad~N","text_ar":"وَدٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wooden pin, peg,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stake; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watidN","text_ar":"وَتِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) of the dial. of Temeem; (IDrd;) or of Nejd: as though they made the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent and incorporated it into the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","Bd"]},{"entry_id":"n41789","headword_ar":"وُدٌّ","root":"wd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wid~N","text_ar":"وِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wad~N","text_ar":"وَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biwud~iY A^ano yakuwna","text_ar":"بِوُدِّى اَنْ يَكُونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I wish that such a thing may be."},{"kind":"text","text":"In the following saying of the poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^ay~uhaA AlEaAy^idu AlmusaAy^ilu Ean~aA\n                      \n                     \n                        wabiwud~iyka lawo varaY A^akofaAniY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O thou visitor of the sick, inquiring respecting us, wishing that thou mayest see my graveclothes"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the kesreh of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":"is lengthened for sake of the measure. (S, L.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%88%D8%AF/","headword_ar":"ود","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=90508#eaef1b","body_html":"<h3>ود</h3><span class=\"sense\">1</span> وَدَّهُ, first <abbr title=\"Persian (Farsi)\">Pers\\.</abbr> وَدِدْتُ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, &amp;c.) and وَدَدْتُ, (<abbr title=\"al-Kisāʾī\">Ks</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Zamakhsharī\">Z</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) [but most disallow this] <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـَ <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> وُدٌّ and وِدٌّ and وَدٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) of which three forms the first is the most common, (<abbr title=\"Muḥammad ibn al-Ṭayyib al-Sharqī al-Fāsī, author of Annotations on the Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">MF</abbr>,) and مَوَدَّةٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) or this last is a simple <abbr title=\"substantive, إِسْمٌ\">subst.</abbr>, (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) and مِوَدَّةٌ (<abbr title=\"The Calcutta edition of the Qāmūs of Firuzabadi\">CK</abbr> and some <abbr title=\"Mukhtār al-Ṣiḥāḥ of al-Rāzī\">MS</abbr>. copies of the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and مَوِدَّةٌ, (<abbr title=\"according\">accord.</abbr> to some other copies of the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, this and the next preceding deviating from the common forms of <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. ns</abbr>., <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) and مَوْدِدَةٌ (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"El-Kazzaz (al-Qazzāz al-Qayrawānī)\">Kz</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and مَوْدَدَةٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) but these last two are allowable only in poetry, and deviate from constant rule, the former doubly, (<abbr title=\"El-Kazzaz (al-Qazzāz al-Qayrawānī)\">Kz</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Muḥammad ibn al-Ṭayyib al-Sharqī al-Fāsī, author of Annotations on the Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">MF</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) and وِدَادٌ and وَدَادٌ and وُدَادٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) the first of which last three forms is the most common, (<abbr title=\"Muḥammad ibn al-Ṭayyib al-Sharqī al-Fāsī, author of Annotations on the Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">MF</abbr>,) and وَدَادَةٌ (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and, <abbr title=\"according\">accord.</abbr> to some, وِدَادَةٌ and وُدَادَةٌ, (<abbr title=\"Muḥammad ibn al-Ṭayyib al-Sharqī al-Fāsī, author of Annotations on the Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">MF</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) and, as in a copy of the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr> esteemed of good authority, مَوْدُودَةٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) He loved, or affected, him, or it, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) i. e. any means of attaining or doing good. (<abbr title=\"al-Azharī, author of the Tahdhīb\">Az</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) The form وَدَدْتُ is disallowed by the Basrees who hold it to be erroneous: and <abbr title=\"Abū Ishāq al-Zajjāj\">Zj</abbr> says, We know that <abbr title=\"al-Kisāʾī\">Ks</abbr> did not mention وَدَدْتُ without having heard it; but he heard it from him who was no authority. (<abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> أَوْدِدْهُ, an imp. form [of ↓ أَوَدَّهُ], without idghám, <abbr title=\"according\">accord.</abbr> to the <abbr title=\"dialect, لُغَةٌ\">dial.</abbr> of El-Hijáz, occurs in a <abbr title=\"tradition (hadith), حَدِيْثٌ\">trad.</abbr>, meaning Love thou it, or affect it. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> وَدِدْتُ لَوْ تَفْعَلُ ذٰلِكَ. and وَدَدْتُ لَوْ أَنَّكَ تَفْعَلُ ذٰلِكَ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> as above, <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> وُدٌّ and وَدٌّ and وَدَادَةٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>) and وَدَادٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>) or وِدَادٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, in <abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb al-Tahdhīb (of Ibn Ḥajar al-ʿAsqalānī)\">TT</abbr>,) I wished that thou wouldest do that. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b4:</span> وَدِدْتُ لَوْ كَانَ كَذَا I wished that it had been so. (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b5:</span> وَدِدْتُ الشَّىْءَ I wished for the thing. <abbr title=\"al-Farrāʾ\">Fr</abbr> says, This is the more approved form; but some say وَدَدْتُ: in both cases the <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> is يَوَدَّ only. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) [Respecting the latter form of the <abbr title=\"preterite, مَاضٍ\">pret.</abbr>, see above.] This is a secondary signification of the verb. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) 3 وادّهُ, <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> مُوَادَّةٌ and وِدَادٌ, He loved, or affected him, being loved, or affected, by him. (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) 4 أَوْدَ3َ see 1.<span class=\"sense\">5</span> تودّدهُ He attracted to himself his love, or affection. (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Aʿrābī\">IAar</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> تودّد إِلَيْهِ He manifested, or showed, love, or affection, to him. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) 6 هُمَا يَتَوَادَّانِ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> تَوَادٌّ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) They two love, or affect, each other. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) وِدٌّ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and ↓ وُدٌّ (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and ↓ وَدٌّ (<abbr title=\"Ibn Jinnī\">IJ</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and ↓ وَدِيدٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) A person loved, or beloved; an object of love; a friend; <abbr title=\"synonym and synonymous, مَرَادفٌ and مَتَرَادِفٌ\">syn.</abbr> خِبٌّ and حَبِيبٌ and صَدِيقٌ (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>) and مُحَبٌّ. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>: in the <abbr title=\"The Calcutta edition of the Qāmūs of Firuzabadi\">CK</abbr> مُحِبٌّ.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> Also, ↓ وُدٌ (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) and ↓ وَدُودٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>) and ↓ وَدِيدٌ (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) and ↓ وَادٌّ (<abbr title=\"El-Kazzaz (al-Qazzāz al-Qayrawānī)\">Kz</abbr>) A person who loves; loving; affectionate: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) the first also used in a <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> sense, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) being [originally] an <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) and the second used alike as <abbr title=\"masculine, مُذَكَّرٌ\">masc</abbr>. and <abbr title=\"feminine, مؤَنَّثٌ\">fem.</abbr> (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> Also, ↓ وُدٌّ and ↓ وُدُودٌ and ↓ مِوَدٌّ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) also written ↓ مَوَدٌّ, (<abbr title=\"Muḥammad ibn al-Ṭayyib al-Sharqī al-Fāsī, author of Annotations on the Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">MF</abbr>,) A man (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) loving much; having much love or affection; very loving or affectionate. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Muḥammad ibn al-Ṭayyib al-Sharqī al-Fāsī, author of Annotations on the Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">MF</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b4:</span> <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">Pl.</abbr> أَوْدَادٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> of وِدٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) and also a <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> [of وُدٌّ] in the second of the above senses; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) and وَدَادٌ, [<abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> of وَدٌّ or وَدِيدٌ] in the first of the above senses; (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>;) and أَوُدٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> of وُدٌّ (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) in the second of the above senses; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) or of وِدٌّ; (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) and أَوْدٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) [an <abbr title=\"irregular\">irreg.</abbr> <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr>, or <abbr title=\"quasi-plural noun, إِسْمُ جَمْعٍ\">quasi-<abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> n.</abbr>, upon which I find no remark,] in the first of the above senses, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) or the second; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) and وُدَّادٌ, <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> of وَادٌّ; (<abbr title=\"El-Kazzaz (al-Qazzāz al-Qayrawānī)\">Kz</abbr>;) and أَوِدَّآءُ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> of وَدِيدٌ (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) in the first of the above senses, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) or in the second; (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>;) and أَوِدَّةٌ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) also <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> of وَدِيدٌ (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) in the second of the above senses; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) and وُدَدَآءُ, <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> of وَدُودٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>) in the second of the above senses, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) [and the third]; and وَدِيدٌ is also mentioned as a <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> in the second of the above senses in the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>; but this is probably a mistake for وِدَادٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b5:</span> <abbr title=\"Ibn al-Athīr al-Jazari\">IAth</abbr> says, that ↓ وُدٌّ, used as an <abbr title=\"نَعْتٌ and وَصْفٌ and صِفَةٌ\">epithet</abbr>, is for ذُو وُدٍّ; but وِدٌّ does not require ذو to be understood, being <abbr title=\"synonymous with, لُغَةٌ فِى\">syn. with</abbr> صَدِيقٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) وَدٌّ: see 1, and وِدٌّ. <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> وَدٌّ and ↓ وُدٌّ (the former is the more common, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>) A certain idol (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) which pertained to the people of Noah, and then to Kelb, and was at Doomet-el-Jendel: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) or a certain good man, who lived between Adam and Noah, and of whom, after his death, was made an image, which, after a long time, became an object of worship; like سُوَاعٌ and يَغُوثُ and يَعُوقُ and نَسْرٌ, mentioned therewith in the <abbr title=\"The Quran\">Kur</abbr>, lxxi. 22 and 23: (<abbr title=\"Al-Bayḍāwī's Exposition of the Quran (Anwār al-Tanzīl)\">Bd</abbr>:) and the former, a certain idol belonging to Kureysh, also called أُدٌّ. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> بِوَدِّكِ By thy Wedd! meaning the idol so named. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> وَدٌّ A wooden pin, peg, or stake; <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> وَتِدٌ: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) of the <abbr title=\"dialect, لُغَةٌ\">dial.</abbr> of Temeem; (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>;) or of Nejd: as though they made the ت quiescent and incorporated it into the د. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>.) وُدٌّ: see 1, and وِدٌّ, and وَدٌّ. <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> بِوُدِّى أَنْ يَكُونَ كَذَا I wish that such a thing may be. In the following saying of the poet, أَيُّهَا العَائِدُ المُسَائِلُ عَنَّا وَبِوُدِّيكَ لَوْ ثَرَى أَكْفَانِى<br><br>[O thou visitor of the sick, inquiring respecting us, wishing that thou mayest see my graveclothes], the kesreh of the د is lengthened for sake of the measure. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) وَدُودٌ: see وِدٌّ. <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> الوَدُودُ, as an <abbr title=\"نَعْتٌ and وَصْفٌ and صِفَةٌ\">epithet</abbr> applied to God, The loving towards his servants, (<abbr title=\"Ibn-El-Ambáree (Abū al-Barakāt Kamāl al-Dīn ibn al-Anbārī)\">IAmb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) or, towards those who obey: (Beyd, lxxxv.<br><br>14:) or He who regards with approbation his righteous servants: or He who is beloved in the hearts of his saints. (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Athīr al-Jazari\">IAth</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) وَدُودٌ also, A mare that puts forth all her power of running. (<abbr title=\"Ibn Sīdah\">ISd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) وَدِيدٌ: see وِدٌّ.<br><br>وَادٌّ: see وِدٌّ.<br><br>أَوَدُّ More or most, loving or affectionate. Said to be also used as a <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr>, for أَوَدُّونَ. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) مَوَدٌّ and مِوَدٌّ: see وِدٌّ.<br><br>مَوَدَّةٌ Love; affection. (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) See also 1. <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> Also, A letter; an epistle: and letters, or epistles: <abbr title=\"synonym and synonymous, مَرَادفٌ and مَتَرَادِفٌ\">syn.</abbr> كِتَابٌ and كُتُبٌ. (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Aʿrābī\">IAar</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) Said to have the latter meaning in the <abbr title=\"The Quran\">Kur</abbr>, lx. 1, in the first of the instances of its occurrence there: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) but this is a strange interpretation. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.)"}]}}